  "texts": [
    "This is exacerbated by the inscrutable nature of many AI systems and the lack of transparency in design practices (Mittelstadt et al. 2016).",
    "Thus, companies often fall back on techno-centric metrics, such as system performance or the click-through rate of users.",
    "Whilst choosing technical metrics to evaluate a system has the benefit of being more quantifiable and measurable, it overlooks human-centred factors such as the users' mental state and well-being that have socio-technical implications.",
    "Through the lack of a holistic measurement to assess a system's effects, insights such as the impact of different design decisions on a user's behaviour and thinking are lost Calvo et al. (2020).",
    "Unsurprisingly, many calls have been made to extend such solely technical focus during the assessment of potential harms of AI-based systems to include broader, socio-technical measures of system effects (McCradden et al. 2020; Chen et al. 2021; Harbers and Overdiek 2022)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
